My usage of the word "God" understandably came across not quite as Intended it, I simply meant that as a convenient name.

As for how you manifest, you must feel yourself into the state of your wish fulfilled. There are a number of different techniques that some favor, however the precise way to do it does not matter. What truly matters is coming to an understanding of your ability, and to feel that you are in the state you desire.

You must first understand what it is that you want, identify your desire. Next, you must use your imagination to figure out how you would feel, if your desire was true.

You live in this state, in the state of the wish fulfilled, and go about your life. You don't stress or concern yourself with the mechanism by which your desire will become a reality, you simply must accept it as essentially already done, it is immanent in your future and there would be nothing you could do to stop it from becoming a reality even if you wanted to.

I am not the best at explaining, but that is the gist of it, here is some further reading that you may take interest in:

https://pastebin.com/pDekUHXM

http://realneville.com/txt/How_To_Use_Your_Imagination.html

Nice, thank you for the reading material.

I use SATS at night before I sleep, and occasionally throughout the day I go into a semi-meditative state and do my manifestations. I simply sit still, tune out the outside world, and place myself into the inevitable future of my desire fulfilled. Once I am satisfied with how I feel about them I return to the world and go about my day.

I must admit frankly that I only very recently even learned about manifestation, and have been practicing it properly for less than a number of weeks. I understand how it may look, me shilling something that I have not even practiced for any prolonged period of time myself, but I was in a relatively hard time when I learned of it and it has helped me to gain immense control over my mind and mental processes since. That is what gives me faith in it's function.

Beyond that, I have only been using manifestation for large, long term desires, such as my dream home in the mountains and my desired anthro woman to be by my side. I still have much progress to be made in the utilization of The Law, however.

Anonymous Thu 18 Feb 2021 23:42:02 No.36441353 Report

>>36439923
I'll dive in now that I'm home.
When you look at the big names in mass-market publishing, they tend to do one of two things. They write what they know, and/or they use their existing experience to leap sideways. And guess what? Many good writers understand the fundamentals of critical thinking. They know how to learn.
In my case, I used to be a semi-professional musician. I wrote music. So while the act of writing a whole story was alien to me, I could understand how paragraphs and scenes were like phrases and movements. I understood a different structure and learned it like a scale or instrument.
Take Michael Crichton. Former medical doctor. Used his basic science chops to build his stories' worlds. Tolkien? Linguist. Used that to build up a fantasy world.
Look at what you know, and figure how to move sideways.

Learn by doing. Start today.

Anonymous Fri 19 Feb 2021 01:29:54 No.36444392 Report
Quoted By:
>>36439923

>>36440503
>>36441353
These.
>Write what you know
A big one, especially for starting a story. Attempting to write about literally anything with a level of authenticity will, for one, give you words to put on the page off the bat. After that, it's difficult to do at all without accidentally getting into the personalities of the characters engaged with it and laying some groundwork context for you to figure out your way forward from. More fundamentally, you also know all the sensations and emotions involved and have a basic idea of how to communicate what your characters will be doing and feeling as such.

That said, don't be afraid to target adjacent topics, just be willing to do the research. Striving for authenticity makes actually writing a lot easier. It's worth it both on your end and for the reader. Degeneracy Pressure was my big experiment with this: The whole story is painstakingly accurate technically, geographically, and visually, but it was pretty much all research. The act of doing the research and having it as context made questions like "how do we advance the story from point b to point c without being retarded or boring" a lot easier to answer. Similarly, don't take "what you know" too literally. Use a little imagination and consider things that are probably look/feel/behave similarly to what you know, and cobble places, scenes, and characters together from fragments of memory. Working from a basis like that helps immensely with starting inertia, writers block, and decision paralysis. Ultimately, the more believable your world is, the easier it will be to navigate for both you and the reader.

>General advice
Remember: writing is an exercise in clarity. Don't worry about depth. Depth results from clarity. Literary devices are really very simple and mechanical. I strongly recommend Perrine's Sound and Sense for a breakdown of these on small scales.

Read up a bit on Stockholm Syndrome
https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Stockholm_syndrome

Search string "stockholm syndrome patty hearst" will yield a very famous case. Not saying you want to do the story about it, but elements of it will be important to be aware of in the idea you sketched out.

Consider that th egang you described has low enough moral standards to plan out and partially implement human trafficking. They could easily be into some fairly rough crime activity that falls short of that. The dynamics and world-building could be fascinating.

One possible event: the gang has this human in captivity (early days). And now they have sympathy for him, feel sad for him and they consider him something of a pet. Would they maybe kidnap a female human in an attempt to give him a companion? How would that work out? Complete disaster, or not? And then the girls running the gang realize that they have certain needs, needs that he can fulfill. Such as glorious-tier grooming and petting. Etc.

Anyway. Post anything you write. Sounds like an entertaining read.
